        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 9:15PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 915 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of East Brewton, or 7 miles east of Brewton, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of eastern Escambia,
southeastern Conecuh and southwestern Covington Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
